This was easy and delicious. I don't know why the complaint of the saltiness, unless the proscuitto was too thick. I even salted the pork before wrapping. The sage leaves had a nice flavor to them when you bite in, I was afraid it would be overpowering but it was really tasty. Only change I made was to add garlic like another reviewer. Also served this with a side of mustard sage cream from the veal recipe on this site.... 2 1/2 tablespoons chopped shallots 1/3 cup unsalted chicken broth 2 tablespoons minced fresh sage or 2 teaspoons dried rubbed sage 2 teaspoons Dijon mustard 1/4 cup half and half (I used fat free...it didn't get thick, but it was yummy!) cooked up with the pan drippings from the pork. Served the sauce in tiny condiment cups on glass dishes.

