Rating: 2
the jamie oliver version of this dish is far superior, and a favorite for wowing guest with very little effort. smash some sage with some garlic in a pestle and mortar, then add a few glugs of olive oil - rub this on your tenderloins and let them sit for a bit, an hour if you have it. then wrap in proscuitto and cover with any remaining marinade, and more sage. he cooks this over rhubarb, but i love it over plums. the resulting juice is simply phenomenal. scrunch up a wet piece of parchment paper and cover the dish the first 15mn of cooking so the proscuitto doesn't burn. the pork always comes out incredibly moist....

